ere increased when a wider scatter window width was used\nfor TEW scatter correction. The width of the scatter windows made a small but\nstatistically significant difference of 1-2% on the recovered $^{177}$Lu\nactivity. Based on these results, we can conclude that activity quantification\nof $^{177}$Lu and lesion detectability is not degraded by the presence of\n$^{90}$Y.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Jan 2023 23:31:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-27"}
