ed to positive emotions. Our findings\nreplicated and extended previous research which suggests that different\nsubregions of the VTA are sensitive to rewarding and aversive stimuli. Taken\ntogether, this study suggests that emotional music embedded in an imagined\nscenario is a salient social signal that prompts preparation of\napproach/avoidance behaviours and emotional responses in listeners.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 Jan 2023 03:01:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-27"}
