ion period of the nucleus using high cadence observations\nand long series of CN images on several nights, and we obtained a value of\n(9.18$\\pm$0.05) hr at perihelion. Using high resolution spectra of 46P coma, we\nderived C and N isotopic ratios of 100$\\pm$20 and 150$\\pm$30 and a green-to-red\nforbidden oxygen [OI] lines ratio of 0.23$\\pm$0.02. We measured a NH$_2$\northo-to-para ratio of 3.31$\\pm$0.03 and derived an ammonia ratio of\n1.19$\\pm$0.03 corresponding to a spin temperature of 27$\\pm$1 K.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 Jan 2023 06:14:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-01"}
